nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speedcenter.informatik.kit.edu/mathlib4/run-detail/f3b99d70-0db7-4a05-ad00-ee2df58abd2f) for commit d4d68b00f927d9b8ecb2d8018671f6b2e2e96f02.
There were [significant changes](http://speedcenter.informatik.kit.edu/mathlib4/compare/15ab5735-f617-498b-ba3e-9fcf2d57b39a/to/f3b99d70-0db7-4a05-ad00-ee2df58abd2f) against commit 63e0da05557d89192561dbb4f60acd348f796968:
```diff
  Benchmark                                                           Metric         Change
  =========================================================================================
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.FilteredColimitCommutesFiniteLimit   instructions    -9.5%
- ~Mathlib.MeasureTheory.CardMeasurableSpace                          instructions     5.0%
- ~Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.Compact                              instructions    10.7%
```

I think this makes sense. Facts in the local context are generally "higher priority", because a human put them there!
